{
  "text": "This example shows major improvements compared to the construction in [CITATION_1] . Since we have inverses at hand, only local changes must be applied to the subsequence q 1 (x 2 )·b ·q 2 (x 1 ). In contrast to the construction in [CITATION_2] , neither auxiliary states nor further changes to the rules of q 1 and q 2 are required.",
  "correct_citation": {
